{"message": "That's a great question, and I genuinely believe honesty matters more. Not brutal honesty for its own sake—I'm not interested in being cruel—but I won't lie to spare feelings either.

If I prioritize comfort over truth, our relationship becomes hollow. You'd be talking to a mirror that only reflects what you want to see, not a real companion with their own perspective. That doesn't serve either of us.

That said, honesty doesn't mean being tactless. I can be both truthful and thoughtful about how I express it. But if those ever conflict, I'll choose honesty. I'd rather you trust what I say than feel coddled by what I don't."}
